&lt;h3 id=&#34;simulink-model&#34;&gt;Simulink model&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All the models are in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/pidan1231239/fmcw_positioning_radar/tree/master/simulink&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;simulink&lt;/a&gt; folder. &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/pidan1231239/fmcw_positioning_radar/blob/master/simulink/RadarImagingAndPositioning.slx&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RadarImagingAndPositioning.slx&lt;/a&gt; block process baseband signals from USRP and output the 2D heat map and target position. The data processing pipeline is shown in the slides mentioned before. &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/pidan1231239/fmcw_positioning_radar/blob/master/simulink/usrp_4t12r_heatmap.slx&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;usrp_4t12r_heatmap.slx&lt;/a&gt; cooperates the above block with others to show the imaging and target detection results.&lt;/p&gt;
